div1.p: In the United States Circuit Court, Superior Court of the State of Ninth Judicial Circuit, Western Dist. of Washington Nothern Division for King County
In the Matter of the Petition of Joseph Walton For a Writ of Habeas Corpus.
Return
Filed in the U.S. Circuit Court. JAN 15 1906, A. Reeves Ayres Clerk.
P. M. Hopkins, Dep.
Kenneth MacKintosh, Attorneys for L. C. Smith, Respondent
In the Circuit Court of the United States for the Ninth Judicial Circuit, Western District of Washington, Northern Division.
In the Matter of the Petition of Joseph Walton for a Writ of Habeas Corpus. No. 1376.

Return.
To the Honorable C.H. Hanford, judge of the above entitled court:

Comes now L.C. Smith, sheriff of King County, Washington, the respondent herein, and resepectfully shows to this honorable court that it is true that on Joseph Walton, petitioner herein, is now and was at the time of the service of said writ, in the custody of this respondent, and that the detention of said petitioner by this respondent is lawful in this:

That said L.C. Smith, sheriff of King County, acting in the public service and not otherwise, did, on the 2nd day of January, 1906, arrest the petitioner herein upon a warrant issued by P.V. Davis, justice of the peace in and for Seatle Precinct, King County, Washington, wherein and whereby this respondent was directed forthwith to apprehend said Joseph Walton, a copy of which warrant is attached to the petition herein and is hereby referred to and made a part of this return; and that said warrant of arrest was issued upon a complaint in due form of law, filed in the justice court in and

for Seattle Precinct, King County, Washington, before P.V. Davis, justice of the peace, wherein and whereby your petitioner was charged with barbering on Sunday, a copy of which complaint is attached to the petition herein and is hereby referred ot and made a part of this return.

Respondent ehrein, having shown to this honorable court that said petitioner is so held by due and lawful process, nevertheless now produces before this honorable court the body of said Joseph walton, petitioner herein, at the time and place as in said writ directed, and hereto attaches and makes a part of this return said writ as upon him served.
Your petitioner prays this honorable court that said writ be now denied, and that the petitioner be held to await the determination of his trial in the justice court herein above referred to.
L. C. Smith, Respondent.
State of Washington, County of King. ss.

L. C. Smith, being first duly sworn, on oath deposes and says that he is the respondent in the foregoing return; that he has read the same, knows the contents thereof, and the same is true as he verily believes.
L. C. Smith
Subscribed and sworn to befroe me this 15th day of January, 1906. Kenneth Macintosh
Notary Public in and for the State of Washington, residing at Seattle in said state.
